MyInterface obj = () -> System.out.println("Hello, Iâ€™m in Functional Interface!");
obj.sayHello();
This is the simplest form â€” now letâ€™s get into the real world!

âš™ï¸ Functional Interface = Lambda Power
Think of Functional Interface like a foundation of functional programming in Java. Lambda expressions give you a short, clean way to implement that one method.

